    "description": "The strategy is a multi speed time series momentum program on liquid futures, designed to harvest persistent trend premia while targeting a stable portfolio level of risk. It trades a fixed universe of two contracts (S and P 500 E mini equity index futures and 10 year US Treasury Note futures) using daily data. Signals are generated from a family of exponentially weighted moving average crossover filters (fast spans as powers of two up to a configurable count, with slow spans four times the fast), converted into risk adjusted forecasts by dividing by an instrument specific daily risk estimate and scaling each horizon to a common forecast scale. Forecasts are then capped using rule specific nonlinear mappings (including special mappings for very fast and very slow horizons) and averaged across horizons with a diversification multiplier to maintain forecast amplitude, producing a single directional forecast per instrument.",
